 "executive_summary": "This study examined how peptide modifications enhance T cell vaccine immunogenicity using the HLA-A2-restricted NY-ESO-1(157-165) tumor epitope and its cognate TCR. A crystal structure of the wild-type peptide\u2013TCR\u2013HLA-A2 complex revealed that TCR recognition is centered on two sequential peptide residues (methionine and tryptophan), and a single C9V anchor substitution that increases MHC binding affinity also subtly repositions the peptide backbone to enhance TCR interactions. The modified analogue peptide shows improved soluble TCR binding and elicits faster lytic-granule polarization, reduced CD8 dependence, and broader cross-reactive CTL responses than the native peptide. These findings demonstrate that rational incorporation of structural data into peptide optimization can generate superagonist variants with enhanced immunogenicity for cancer immunotherapy, with implications for T cell vaccine design.",
